text:
At the height of Black Lives Matter protests in New York City, the police were repeatedly filmed using force against peaceful protesters.

We reviewed more than 60 videos. In many, force did not appear warranted. This thread contains scenes of violence. https://t.co/H2zSIgal8Q

name: nytimes
text:
A short video does not tell the whole story.

It's unclear, for example, what the NYPD officers’ intentions were or why protesters were being arrested or told to move. We also don't know what happened before the camera started rolling. https://t.co/931x13EQs6

name: nytimes
text:
